  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agricultural Sector Programme Support (ASPS), Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the agricultural sector-programme in Uganda was to improve the livelihoods of farmers by increasing income and provide food security. The programme has especially been targeted women, which represents the majority of Uganda&#xBF;s farmers. The new Growth-programme, build on experiences and results from the agricultural sector-programme.

The agricultural sector-programme has contributed to the implementation of an agricultural insurance reform in Uganda, whilst contributing to the design of the national Agricultural Consultancy. Furthermore, support has been allocated towards five district councils for agricultural training and information. Likewise, the Ministry of Agriculture has received institutional support, in order to assist the government&#xBF;s modernisation of the agricultural sector. Support to agro-business has been another focal point. The objective has been to stimulate the private sector so that it will engage and play a more prominent role in agricultural development. The contribution centres on capacity building of financial institutions and loan guarantees; support to agro-business and unions, including the development of their commercial activities. Finally, the programme has successfully contributed to the reconstruction of agriculture in the fragile and impoverished Northern Uganda.</narrative>
  </description>
